Durban - Five people were treated for smoke inhalation and burn wounds by paramedics after a fire spread through an informal settlement in Sea Cow Lake north of Durban on Thursday. Robert Mckenzie a spokesperson for the KwaZulu-Natal Emergency Medical Services (EMS) said the fire broke out at the Joanna Road informal settlement which spreads up a steep embankment. He said the exact cause of the fire was unknown. He said firefighters contained and then cut of the fire from spreading "We have treated five patients at the scene. They were in a stable condition and did not want to be taken to hospital. The fire was extinguished. The firefightersÂ from the eThekwini Municipality Fire and Emergency Services were still on the scene damping down. There is alot of smoke coming out from the twisted metal sheets because of the heat of the fire," Mckenzie said. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
